Heat exchanger.Description: Heat exchangers contain fluids that transfer heat between two or more streams.
Heat exchangers consist of tubes through which the fluid flows, facilitating heat transfer.
Heat exchangers consist of a shell that encloses the tubes and provides structural support.
Heat exchangers utilize heat transfer surfaces to enhance the efficiency of heat exchange.
